1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:47,965
CHAPTER 19:
YOU JUST HAVE SUCH GOOD CHEMISTRY

2
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:52,678
EPISODE 6

3
00:00:53,721 --> 00:00:55,514
This can't be real.

4
00:00:55,598 --> 00:00:56,807
It's just a dream.

5
00:00:56,891 --> 00:00:59,310
There's no way this is really happening.

6
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:00,811
It just can't be.

7
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:07,234
I just want to die.

8
00:01:07,318 --> 00:01:10,654
Why did it have to be him?

9
00:01:10,738 --> 00:01:12,740
I'm so embarrassed.

10
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:14,617
This is so humiliating.

11
00:01:15,576 --> 00:01:18,204
Why is he still reading?

12
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:21,707
Is he enjoying it?

13
00:01:23,209 --> 00:01:24,043
What?

14
00:01:24,752 --> 00:01:25,586
Sorry?

15
00:01:26,545 --> 00:01:27,546
What!

16
00:01:37,264 --> 00:01:40,434
He's supposed to be a genius.
Is he a genius at torture too?

17
00:01:40,518 --> 00:01:43,020
Making me die of humiliation
without a single visible wound?

18
00:01:52,196 --> 00:01:54,031
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Yes, sir?

19
00:01:55,241 --> 00:01:56,450
What's this?

20
00:01:56,534 --> 00:01:57,368
Sorry, sir?

21
00:02:01,789 --> 00:02:03,040
I asked what this is.

22
00:02:08,671 --> 00:02:09,713
The thing is.

23
00:02:10,506 --> 00:02:13,884
It looks like someone
was working on a web novel.

24
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:16,887
-Indeed.
-Yes.

25
00:02:17,847 --> 00:02:19,431
Yes, well.

26
00:02:19,515 --> 00:02:22,351
I was pretty surprised myself.

27
00:02:22,434 --> 00:02:24,103
Gosh, that's just nasty…

28
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,063
It's not yours?

29
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:26,981
No, sir.

30
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:28,941
I didn't write it.

31
00:02:29,024 --> 00:02:31,485
Like someone who admits to drinking
but denies drunk driving.

32
00:02:32,111 --> 00:02:34,488
You've been caught red-handed,
yet you deny it?

33
00:02:38,576 --> 00:02:41,495
The clueless Korean lit. major Choi Yoon
is Dong-ju.

34
00:02:41,579 --> 00:02:42,997
The complete asshole…

35
00:02:46,709 --> 00:02:48,210
of a math genius Ju Si-on is me.

36
00:02:49,253 --> 00:02:50,838
The dumb sports major Kang Tae-ha,

37
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:53,424
who solves everything with force,
is Gi-jeon.

38
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:56,385
And Han Jae-min,
who comes from Japan and is loaded,

39
00:02:57,177 --> 00:02:58,012
is Da-ju.

40
00:03:00,055 --> 00:03:01,974
No.

41
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:03,976
How did you come to that conclusion?

42
00:03:06,312 --> 00:03:07,980
"I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause."

43
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:08,898
"I'm very disappointed."

44
00:03:08,981 --> 00:03:10,774
"It was clearly your fault
and you've admitted it."

45
00:03:10,858 --> 00:03:12,359
"All that's left is compensation."

46
00:03:12,443 --> 00:03:14,904
"Breaking my glasses caused
ten million won's worth of damage."

47
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:16,906
"You'll have to find another way
to repay me."

48
00:03:18,824 --> 00:03:21,702
All that being word for word what I said
is a coincidence?

49
00:03:24,914 --> 00:03:27,291
"You wouldn't let him sleep.
Don't you know he's a sleepyhead?"

50
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:29,585
Da-ju said that in the car
on the way to school.

51
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:30,961
Is this all just a coincidence?

52
00:03:31,337 --> 00:03:33,464
Or is my imagination running wild?

53
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:36,508
You just have such good chemistry.

54
00:03:38,761 --> 00:03:39,678
What?

55
00:03:39,762 --> 00:03:41,305
You all have such good chemistry.

56
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:43,057
So I just wrote about it.

57
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,058
But the thing is…

58
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:46,685
People really liked it, so…

59
00:03:50,022 --> 00:03:52,483
Even if you can't tell
right from wrong, still…

60
00:03:52,566 --> 00:03:54,401
There's a line you shouldn't cross.

61
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:56,612
I'm sorry.

62
00:03:57,363 --> 00:03:58,530
Delete it.

63
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:01,116
Sorry?

64
00:04:02,493 --> 00:04:03,410
I can't, sir.

65
00:04:04,203 --> 00:04:05,037
You can't?

66
00:04:06,914 --> 00:04:08,040
No, I can't.

67
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:09,750
I can't.

68
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,168
Please forgive me.

69
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,795
I really can't delete it.

70
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:15,214
I'm really sorry. It was a mistake,
but I can't delete it.

71
00:04:15,798 --> 00:04:17,424
You base your characters on your teachers

72
00:04:17,508 --> 00:04:20,761
and even have them say things
I can't even bring myself to say.

73
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:21,971
How can I let that slide?

74
00:04:22,054 --> 00:04:23,430
Put yourself in my position.

75
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:25,599
Even so.

76
00:04:26,809 --> 00:04:28,060
I can't delete it.

77
00:04:28,727 --> 00:04:29,853
I really can't.

78
00:04:31,397 --> 00:04:32,231
Fine.

79
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:35,150
Then I will.

80
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:40,823
PASSWORD

81
00:04:45,327 --> 00:04:46,537
Enter your password.

82
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:49,540
Mr. Ga.

83
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:53,168
I'll study really hard.

84
00:04:53,252 --> 00:04:55,838
I'll study math really hard.

85
00:04:55,921 --> 00:04:57,172
Please, give me a break.

86
00:04:57,256 --> 00:04:58,841
Even the dying get one last wish.

87
00:04:58,924 --> 00:05:01,969
Can't you do one favor
to help out a pitiful student?

88
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:04,346
I put my life and soul into writing it.

89
00:05:04,430 --> 00:05:06,306
How can I just delete it?

90
00:05:07,141 --> 00:05:09,018
Please cut me a break.

91
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,521
I really can't delete it.

92
00:05:13,731 --> 00:05:16,483
I can't delete it.

93
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:18,485
Please.

94
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,948
What am I going to do?

95
00:05:26,201 --> 00:05:27,494
I'm so sorry.

96
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:37,087
30 MINUTES LATER

97
00:05:51,769 --> 00:05:52,895
If you really can't delete it,

98
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:57,900
bring your parents to see me.

99
00:05:59,443 --> 00:06:00,486
-Sorry?
-If you're okay

100
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:02,071
with your parents, the principal,

101
00:06:02,154 --> 00:06:04,740
the faculty and all the students
knowing what you've been up to.

102
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:06,617
No, sir.

103
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,077
My mom will kill me.

104
00:06:09,495 --> 00:06:11,538
It seems you know
what you've done is wrong.

105
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:17,127
Why do you want to keep doing something
you can't tell anyone about?

106
00:06:19,505 --> 00:06:22,382
I'm going to check tomorrow,
so either delete it or bring your parents.

107
00:06:24,843 --> 00:06:26,053
Sir!

108
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:46,240
CHAPTER 20: THE OBSESSIVE TOP DOESN'T EVEN
HAVE A TOILET IN HIS BATHROOM

109
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:00,379
I'm home.

110
00:07:02,381 --> 00:07:03,757
I made galbijjim.

111
00:07:05,509 --> 00:07:06,760
I'm not hungry.

112
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:10,472
What's wrong? Are you sick?

113
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:12,516
No.

114
00:07:13,684 --> 00:07:16,645
Shall I make you tteokbokki instead?

115
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:17,980
I'm fine.

116
00:07:26,155 --> 00:07:27,156
Shall I delete it?

117
00:07:29,992 --> 00:07:30,868
No, I can't.

118
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:34,746
Then everyone will find out what I wrote.

119
00:07:34,830 --> 00:07:38,500
Still, isn't that better than deleting it?

120
00:07:39,835 --> 00:07:42,838
Am I crazy? It's better to delete it.

121
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:56,768
-You're home?
-Yeah.

122
00:07:58,395 --> 00:08:00,314
-Hey.
-Hey.

123
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:12,826
Tae-ha caressed Yoon's snow-white skin…

124
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:16,747
tenderly.

125
00:08:20,459 --> 00:08:22,628
Hey! Sit apart.

126
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:24,671
I said sit apart.

127
00:08:25,464 --> 00:08:27,049
-What's wrong?
-You startled me.

128
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:29,343
Wanna play?

129
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,178
No, I can't.

130
00:08:31,261 --> 00:08:33,180
-Just one round.
-No, I need to get to bed.

131
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:35,015
I know you want to.

132
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:36,225
Just a quickie.

133
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:37,935
Wanna

134
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:41,271
-play?
-Just a quickie.

135
00:08:49,655 --> 00:08:50,781
Let me join in.

136
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:52,658
-The three of us?
-Move.

137
00:08:53,325 --> 00:08:54,993
Was it leg day today? Nice.

138
00:08:56,328 --> 00:08:57,204
No.

139
00:08:57,913 --> 00:08:59,456
Not two of you, nor three of you.

140
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:01,375
Just play by yourself.

141
00:09:03,669 --> 00:09:05,128
What do you mean play by ourselves?

142
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:07,172
What's wrong with you?

143
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:10,509
You want to play too?
We can change partners.

144
00:09:10,592 --> 00:09:11,885
I'm disgusting.

145
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:14,471
My mind. My imagination.

146
00:09:15,973 --> 00:09:17,599
What on earth was all that?

147
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:29,695
BOYS' LOVE

148
00:09:29,778 --> 00:09:32,781
This is for all teachers and students.

149
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:35,242
Just to inform you
that eleventh-grader Yeo Eui-ju

150
00:09:35,325 --> 00:09:40,872
has been writing a BL web novel
titled We Were Friends.

151
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:43,750
BL?

152
00:09:43,834 --> 00:09:46,670
You told me you didn't like that.
Were you lying?

153
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:47,838
Go-ya!

154
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:49,047
Disgusting.

155
00:09:49,631 --> 00:09:51,591
Pretending to be all sweet and innocent.

156
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:53,593
Why pair a guy with another guy?

157
00:09:54,177 --> 00:09:55,470
-No.
-Eui-ju.

158
00:09:58,515 --> 00:09:59,391
Mom.

159
00:10:00,642 --> 00:10:01,810
What's wrong?

160
00:10:02,394 --> 00:10:03,228
Mom, I…

161
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:09,776
This is a crime.

162
00:10:09,860 --> 00:10:12,321
You've tarnished my name and my honor.

163
00:10:12,404 --> 00:10:14,197
I hope you rot in jail.

164
00:10:14,281 --> 00:10:15,574
I made a mistake.

165
00:10:16,408 --> 00:10:17,409
Are you crazy?

166
00:10:18,035 --> 00:10:20,078
Idle hands are the devil's playthings.

167
00:10:20,162 --> 00:10:21,204
It gives me the creeps.

168
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:22,831
Eui-ju.

169
00:10:23,832 --> 00:10:25,375
No.

170
00:10:25,459 --> 00:10:26,668
No, sir.

171
00:10:26,752 --> 00:10:27,961
It's not like that.

172
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,426
I'm sorry.

173
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:35,594
I'm sorry.

174
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:37,971
My daughter didn't do anything wrong.

175
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:40,766
She learned from me.

176
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:42,851
-It's all my fault.
-Dad…

177
00:10:52,069 --> 00:10:53,570
No!

178
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,822
What's this?

179
00:10:56,948 --> 00:10:58,283
Let me go!

180
00:11:00,744 --> 00:11:03,288
Don't come any closer.

181
00:11:11,755 --> 00:11:12,714
No.

182
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:15,092
No.

183
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,219
I must never be outed.

184
00:11:18,095 --> 00:11:20,472
It seems you know
what you've done is wrong.

185
00:11:21,139 --> 00:11:23,809
Why do you want to keep doing something
you can't tell anyone about?

186
00:11:29,147 --> 00:11:30,982
Boys' love…

187
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:34,986
"The character with the biggest fan base
is the obsessive exhibitionist."

188
00:11:35,779 --> 00:11:39,408
"He lives in a marble penthouse
where the lights are always off."

189
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:44,663
"He's cut ties with his family
and has no friends."

190
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,833
"When he showers,
he only ever uses the rain shower head."

191
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:50,627
"In his bathroom, there's…"

192
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:52,921
NO TOILET

193
00:11:53,505 --> 00:11:54,339
"…no toilet?"

194
00:11:57,134 --> 00:11:57,968
Why not?

195
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:03,765
Why did I have to get caught

196
00:12:03,849 --> 00:12:06,143
by that asshole of a math teacher?

197
00:12:11,606 --> 00:12:16,570
Ga Woo-su!

198
00:12:24,828 --> 00:12:25,871
Good morning.

199
00:12:34,212 --> 00:12:35,213
Follow me.

200
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:44,639
COUNSELING IN PROGRESS

201
00:12:44,723 --> 00:12:45,765
Did you delete it?

202
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:52,939
Mr. Ga.

203
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:57,444
I started writing web novels
when I was in eighth grade.

204
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:01,156
And?

205
00:13:01,865 --> 00:13:06,786
It was just a crappy story I made by
cobbling together bits and pieces I liked.

206
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:11,791
But I decided to upload it
to the Challenge League.

207
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:13,793
Then, out of the blue, it got

208
00:13:13,877 --> 00:13:14,878
two favorites.

209
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:18,048
I got so excited that
I did a mass release of two more episodes.

210
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:22,844
What I mean by that

211
00:13:22,928 --> 00:13:24,763
is in quick succession.

212
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:28,558
You have to be quick with
the first few episodes to generate

213
00:13:28,642 --> 00:13:29,726
a buzz.

214
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:32,145
Anyhow, the number of favorites

215
00:13:32,229 --> 00:13:33,688
went straight back down to one.

216
00:13:33,772 --> 00:13:35,398
They must have seen the next two episodes

217
00:13:36,608 --> 00:13:37,442
and done a runner.

218
00:13:37,526 --> 00:13:39,402
10 MINUTES LATER

219
00:13:40,403 --> 00:13:42,822
These days, do you know what I think

220
00:13:42,906 --> 00:13:44,366
when I wake up in the morning?

221
00:13:46,243 --> 00:13:48,370
I can see the light
at the end of the tunnel.

222
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:52,249
What I thought was a dead-end cave
was actually a tunnel.

223
00:13:52,874 --> 00:13:55,961
The cold and lonely winter

224
00:13:57,045 --> 00:14:00,048
is finally coming to an end
and flowers are going to bloom.

225
00:14:01,716 --> 00:14:05,178
Mr. Ga, this novel

226
00:14:05,262 --> 00:14:08,848
gives me hope
and is a dream I can't give up.

227
00:14:08,932 --> 00:14:11,643
Can you please help me
make my dream come true?

228
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:13,979
Can you please help me finish my novel?

229
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:16,022
No.

230
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:17,941
Just this once.

231
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:19,526
Just this once, please.

232
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:24,114
Are you saying you intend to keep writing
the sort of things I would never say?

233
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:26,992
The sort of stuff that gives me the ick
and sets my teeth on edge?

234
00:14:31,663 --> 00:14:32,539
Are you crying?

235
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:33,665
No, sir.

236
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:37,252
I know I did wrong.

237
00:14:38,461 --> 00:14:42,090
But how can I delete it?
It's got more than 20,000 favorites.

238
00:14:43,842 --> 00:14:46,761
Anyone would think I'm the bad guy here.
I'm the victim!

239
00:14:47,387 --> 00:14:49,055
Of all the different genres,

240
00:14:50,765 --> 00:14:52,434
why did it have to be BL?

241
00:14:53,226 --> 00:14:57,480
Because the more I heard "No, no,"
the more I want to encourage them,

242
00:14:57,564 --> 00:15:01,276
and even just the slightest brush
of a fingertip creates a deep yearning.

243
00:15:03,486 --> 00:15:05,196
Do you even know what you did wrong?

244
00:15:05,864 --> 00:15:06,781
Yes, I do.

245
00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:08,908
I do know.

246
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:12,787
But if you look at it from a more worldly
point-of-view, love is love.

247
00:15:12,871 --> 00:15:15,624
When two people love each other,
gender isn't that important.

248
00:15:15,707 --> 00:15:17,000
Not that.

249
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:20,211
Not that?

250
00:15:20,295 --> 00:15:21,963
Then, the raunchiness?

251
00:15:22,047 --> 00:15:23,882
But it's not even rated 15.

252
00:15:23,965 --> 00:15:26,051
Even the publisher said it's mild.

253
00:15:26,134 --> 00:15:27,093
Mild!

254
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:29,804
Not that either?

255
00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:34,267
Making my teachers the main characters?

256
00:15:34,351 --> 00:15:37,020
Yes, that was a huge mistake on my part.

257
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:38,688
And I'm really sorry about that, but--

258
00:15:38,772 --> 00:15:40,565
You really are a lost cause.

259
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:45,278
You still don't know what you did wrong.

260
00:15:45,362 --> 00:15:47,030
How can you not know?

261
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:47,947
I'm sorry.

262
00:15:48,031 --> 00:15:49,157
I just don't get it.

263
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:51,993
How is it?

264
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:53,995
Why on earth…

265
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:57,749
Am I not the main character?

266
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:02,128
Sorry?

267
00:16:03,588 --> 00:16:06,007
You're going to have Dong-ju and Gi-jeon
end up together.

268
00:16:06,091 --> 00:16:07,133
Where does that leave me?

269
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:11,096
You're a sub character.

270
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,348
A sub.

271
00:16:15,934 --> 00:16:17,977
I've never been a sub my whole life.

272
00:16:19,854 --> 00:16:20,855
Sorry?

273
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:22,857
I want you to rewrite it.

274
00:16:22,941 --> 00:16:24,109
With me

275
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:26,027
as the main character.

276
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:30,407
-What?
-You know what the main character is.

277
00:16:32,075 --> 00:16:34,035
You want to be the obsessive top?

278
00:16:36,287 --> 00:16:37,539
If that's the main character.

279
00:16:40,709 --> 00:16:42,669
Then the story will go off the rails.

280
00:16:42,752 --> 00:16:44,504
I don't care if it jumps the shark,

281
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:46,798
just know that I'm going to check
each and every episode.

282
00:16:48,675 --> 00:16:51,761
Sir, you can't check it in advance.
I simply can't allow it.

283
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:54,681
Why not?

284
00:16:54,764 --> 00:16:55,724
Well…

285
00:16:56,891 --> 00:16:59,894
If I know you're going to be reading,

286
00:16:59,978 --> 00:17:01,980
how can I write that kind of stuff?

287
00:17:02,063 --> 00:17:03,189
Then delete it.

288
00:17:12,615 --> 00:17:14,075
You have two choices.

289
00:17:14,159 --> 00:17:16,077
Delete it or let me check each episode.

290
00:17:16,161 --> 00:17:17,495
What are you going to do?

291
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:23,293
I'll do it.

292
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:24,961
I'll let you check it.

293
00:17:30,842 --> 00:17:32,010
What am I going to do?

294
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:46,941
So he's mad, not because it's BL,

295
00:17:47,025 --> 00:17:49,736
but because he isn't the main character?

296
00:17:52,155 --> 00:17:54,157
He's not normal.

297
00:17:54,783 --> 00:17:57,243
He must be crazy.

298
00:17:57,327 --> 00:17:59,078
EBC FILMING PROPOSAL

299
00:17:59,162 --> 00:18:00,830
CHAPTER 21:
YOU REALLY THINK WOO-SU WILL DO IT?

300
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:04,292
3. OBJECTIVE

301
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:07,295
Come in.

302
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,465
Do come in.

303
00:18:10,965 --> 00:18:12,342
Have a seat.

304
00:18:15,386 --> 00:18:16,262
Take a look.

305
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:22,602
EBC is coming here to film?

306
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:24,020
Finally.

307
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:27,065
Next Monday,
the makers of that hit program

308
00:18:27,148 --> 00:18:30,068
are coming to film at our school.

309
00:18:33,404 --> 00:18:36,699
You four teachers
are the pride of our school.

310
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:39,327
You're all elite teachers
with impressive resumes.

311
00:18:39,410 --> 00:18:44,582
When you're filmed teaching the kids
with your endless passion and dedication,

312
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:48,336
the foundation's donors are sure
to start writing checks, right, Dong-ju?

313
00:18:48,419 --> 00:18:50,129
Sorry? Me?

314
00:18:50,213 --> 00:18:53,174
I want you to write an essay
setting out your philosophy of education.

315
00:18:53,258 --> 00:18:55,176
One that elicits emotion.

316
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:57,512
Enough to make people cry.

317
00:18:58,513 --> 00:19:00,139
Yes, ma'am.

318
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,517
And as for you, Gi-jeon.

319
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,352
Prepare a few words about your path

320
00:19:04,435 --> 00:19:07,230
from retiring as a professional athlete
to become a teacher.

321
00:19:07,313 --> 00:19:09,440
Yes, ma'am.

322
00:19:09,524 --> 00:19:12,485
-Next, Da-ju.
-Yes.

323
00:19:12,569 --> 00:19:14,445
Do you think you can rehash

324
00:19:14,529 --> 00:19:16,865
your TUD talk?

325
00:19:16,948 --> 00:19:20,952
Your grand vision
is sure to go down in history.

326
00:19:21,536 --> 00:19:23,705
-Down in history.
-Down in history.

327
00:19:24,539 --> 00:19:27,417
And last but not least, Woo-su.

328
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,669
What more needs to be said?

329
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:32,171
You're the very definition
of a global elite.

330
00:19:32,255 --> 00:19:35,967
We just need to change your glasses.

331
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:39,345
-And in class--
-I won't be taking part.

332
00:19:41,723 --> 00:19:42,932
Sorry?

333
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,561
I don't want to film.

334
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:49,397
But I'll cooperate in another way
if there's any.

335
00:19:50,607 --> 00:19:51,774
Woo-su.

336
00:19:53,401 --> 00:19:54,736
I guess you didn't hear me.

337
00:19:58,823 --> 00:20:00,950
This program will be on EBC.

338
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:04,746
If you don't agree to film,

339
00:20:04,829 --> 00:20:06,497
that's going to be a problem.

340
00:20:07,081 --> 00:20:07,957
I'm sorry.

341
00:20:08,583 --> 00:20:09,584
That won't be possible.

342
00:20:12,253 --> 00:20:14,422
Still, for the sake of
the school's future development,

343
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:16,382
please take some time to reconsider.

344
00:20:16,466 --> 00:20:18,092
I believe I've made myself clear.

345
00:20:18,176 --> 00:20:20,303
If you've nothing more to say,
I'll be on my way.

346
00:20:27,185 --> 00:20:28,603
Don't worry, Ms. Kim.

347
00:20:29,354 --> 00:20:30,688
I'll convince him.

348
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:32,857
Da-ju.

349
00:20:34,484 --> 00:20:35,777
If you wouldn't mind.

350
00:20:36,903 --> 00:20:38,863
I want the four of you

351
00:20:38,947 --> 00:20:41,240
including Woo-su to be on camera.

352
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:45,536
There's a week until filming,
I'm sure you can do it.

353
00:20:46,621 --> 00:20:48,206
-Yes.
-Of course.

354
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:49,832
Don't worry.

355
00:20:56,339 --> 00:20:57,465
What are you going to do?

356
00:20:58,091 --> 00:20:59,258
Got any ideas?

357
00:21:00,343 --> 00:21:01,302
Of course, he doesn't.

358
00:21:02,512 --> 00:21:04,138
Couldn't just the three of us do it?

359
00:21:04,222 --> 00:21:06,307
You heard what the principal said.

360
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,435
There's no point without Woo-su.

361
00:21:10,228 --> 00:21:13,314
We're basically Ga Woo-su and Boys.

362
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:16,150
You really think Woo-su will do it?

363
00:21:16,234 --> 00:21:18,403
You know him better than anyone.

364
00:21:18,486 --> 00:21:20,321
Why did you say you'd convince him?

365
00:21:20,405 --> 00:21:22,156
At this school,

366
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:25,368
upsetting the principal

367
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:27,578
is a fate worse than death.

368
00:21:28,371 --> 00:21:29,539
If Woo-su won't film,

369
00:21:30,873 --> 00:21:32,208
we'll all end up being fired.

370
00:21:33,751 --> 00:21:35,003
No way.

371
00:21:36,713 --> 00:21:37,755
You think?

372
00:21:43,845 --> 00:21:46,097
Hey, Woo-su.

373
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:47,098
Not doing it.

374
00:21:47,682 --> 00:21:48,975
Just this once.

375
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:50,393
It'll be over in no time.

376
00:21:52,729 --> 00:21:54,022
How can you even say that?

377
00:21:54,105 --> 00:21:55,398
You of all people.

378
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:56,983
You think I want to do this?

379
00:21:57,066 --> 00:21:59,277
I've known you since third grade.

380
00:21:59,902 --> 00:22:01,612
I know what happened better than anyone.

381
00:22:01,696 --> 00:22:03,322
Then don't make me say it again.

382
00:22:03,406 --> 00:22:04,240
Get out.

383
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,577
Woo-su, don't make me
get down on my knees and beg.

384
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:09,579
Don't bother. Now get out.

385
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:12,707
Fine.

386
00:22:27,221 --> 00:22:28,097
WE WERE FRIENDS

387
00:22:34,645 --> 00:22:37,315
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 3

388
00:22:38,274 --> 00:22:40,068
When is she going to upload episode four?

389
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:46,282
CHAPTER 22: DO I REALLY HAVE TO CHANGE
THIS FOR YOU TO FEEL VALIDATED?

390
00:22:46,866 --> 00:22:48,409
Now that he's going to check my work,

391
00:22:48,493 --> 00:22:51,162
how am I supposed to write
all the flirty stuff?

392
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:57,001
I refuse to breathe
until we get episode four!

393
00:22:57,085 --> 00:22:58,836
Do you feel the tension between these two?

394
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,630
Hurry up and upload episode four!

395
00:23:00,713 --> 00:23:02,715
When is episode four coming out?

396
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:27,323
Where's episode four?

397
00:23:28,866 --> 00:23:31,494
Where's the "mass release"?
Have you lost your spark?

398
00:23:32,995 --> 00:23:33,955
I'm sorry, sir.

399
00:23:34,038 --> 00:23:35,540
There's no need to apologize to me.

400
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:38,835
Try to understand how Si-on feels.

401
00:23:38,918 --> 00:23:40,461
What he likes and how he grew up.

402
00:23:40,545 --> 00:23:43,756
What he thinks about Yoon.

403
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:45,466
Concentrate on Si-on.

404
00:23:58,229 --> 00:23:59,689
I hear EBC is gonna film at school.

405
00:23:59,772 --> 00:24:02,191
I hope Dong-ju doesn't become famous.

406
00:24:06,154 --> 00:24:07,446
Where are you going?

407
00:24:32,471 --> 00:24:33,431
MATHEMATICS

408
00:24:41,022 --> 00:24:43,858
Why do you get nervous and run away
every time you see Mr. Ga?

409
00:24:45,026 --> 00:24:46,485
Me?

410
00:24:46,569 --> 00:24:47,403
What do you mean?

411
00:24:48,029 --> 00:24:49,113
No, I don't.

412
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:57,205
-Where did we get to?
-We're up to page 101.

413
00:24:57,288 --> 00:24:58,122
Page 101.

414
00:24:58,915 --> 00:25:00,625
Velocity and acceleration.

415
00:25:06,797 --> 00:25:08,299
He's so hardcore.

416
00:25:08,382 --> 00:25:10,843
How can he ride her like that
just for getting four points?

417
00:25:10,927 --> 00:25:12,220
A lot of kids gave up on math.

418
00:25:12,303 --> 00:25:14,305
But Eui-ju's the only one
that took the bait.

419
00:25:15,723 --> 00:25:18,643
It's not just the after-school class.
She seems to be really stressed.

420
00:25:26,734 --> 00:25:29,904
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

421
00:25:31,197 --> 00:25:35,034
THE DOOR TO THE PENTHOUSE OPENS
TO REVEAL A LONG CORRIDOR

422
00:25:37,453 --> 00:25:41,832
HIS HAND CLUTCHING THE STRAP ON HIS BAG,
YOON APPROACHES TAE-HA

423
00:25:41,916 --> 00:25:44,001
I told you not to be late.
Not even a second.

424
00:25:45,086 --> 00:25:45,920
I'm sorry.

425
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:47,755
I ran here so as not to be late.

426
00:25:47,838 --> 00:25:49,257
Were you with Si-on?

427
00:25:50,341 --> 00:25:52,927
YOON COULDN'T BRING HIMSELF TO ANSWER

428
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:55,179
HIS SILENCE WAS ENOUGH OF AN ANSWER

429
00:25:58,766 --> 00:25:59,725
This won't do.

430
00:26:00,351 --> 00:26:01,227
Choi Yoon.

431
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:04,021
This place is huge.

432
00:26:04,105 --> 00:26:05,356
You live here alone?

433
00:26:07,233 --> 00:26:08,651
What about that ten million?

434
00:26:09,402 --> 00:26:11,404
Why are you being like this, Tae-ha?

435
00:26:12,697 --> 00:26:14,031
This isn't you.

436
00:26:16,826 --> 00:26:19,495
I'm not the same guy
who hung on your every word.

437
00:26:20,871 --> 00:26:23,291
I'm not the same guy
who ran to you like a puppy.

438
00:26:24,625 --> 00:26:25,584
Not anymore.

439
00:26:26,544 --> 00:26:27,837
Tae-ha.

440
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:28,754
No.

441
00:26:30,923 --> 00:26:31,757
I could be

442
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:33,509
your puppy.

443
00:26:34,885 --> 00:26:35,845
From now on,

444
00:26:36,846 --> 00:26:39,015
I'll be your personal bitch.

445
00:26:40,933 --> 00:26:43,477
FROM NOW ON, I'LL BE YOUR PERSONAL BITCH

446
00:26:48,816 --> 00:26:51,819
I made the right choice.

447
00:26:51,902 --> 00:26:53,571
This is better than deleting it.

448
00:26:54,363 --> 00:26:56,657
When faced with a difficult choice,

449
00:26:56,741 --> 00:26:58,659
taking the more difficult path

450
00:26:58,743 --> 00:27:00,161
is the way to salvation.

451
00:27:00,244 --> 00:27:02,830
No, I'm dying here.

452
00:27:16,719 --> 00:27:18,095
If it's the penthouse,

453
00:27:18,721 --> 00:27:20,473
shouldn't that be where Si-on lives?

454
00:27:21,515 --> 00:27:22,641
Sorry?

455
00:27:24,060 --> 00:27:24,894
What did I say?

456
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:29,565
Si-on should be the main character.

457
00:27:29,648 --> 00:27:30,608
Again.

458
00:27:31,275 --> 00:27:33,402
Si-on should be the main character.

459
00:27:33,486 --> 00:27:34,487
Right. From now on,

460
00:27:34,570 --> 00:27:36,947
Si-on is the obsessive lead
and Tae-ha the regretful sub.

461
00:27:37,031 --> 00:27:39,950
Give all the key impactful lines to Si-on.

462
00:27:40,034 --> 00:27:41,744
Rewrite it with Tae-ha's role minimized.

463
00:27:46,499 --> 00:27:47,333
Now.

464
00:27:49,627 --> 00:27:50,961
Here?

465
00:27:52,963 --> 00:27:53,964
You've got one hour.

466
00:27:59,970 --> 00:28:00,846
Get away from him.

467
00:28:03,307 --> 00:28:04,225
What?

468
00:28:09,230 --> 00:28:11,357
It can't be helped
if you've got feelings for Tae-ha.

469
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,150
But I won't stand idly by.

470
00:28:13,234 --> 00:28:14,151
From now on,

471
00:28:14,985 --> 00:28:17,613
I'll be your personal bitch.

472
00:28:21,659 --> 00:28:23,119
Hang on a second.

473
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:24,078
This feels wrong.

474
00:28:27,373 --> 00:28:28,249
Sorry?

475
00:28:31,168 --> 00:28:33,087
What's wrong?

476
00:28:33,170 --> 00:28:36,006
Shouldn't this be Tae-ha's line?

477
00:28:40,177 --> 00:28:43,055
I know it feels a little awkward.

478
00:28:44,306 --> 00:28:45,474
Still, let's stick with it.

479
00:28:45,558 --> 00:28:48,477
Yoon needs to realize Si-on isn't the one.

480
00:28:48,561 --> 00:28:50,646
This isn't the first time
he's been gaslit.

481
00:28:51,272 --> 00:28:52,857
It's really frustrating.

482
00:28:52,940 --> 00:28:57,069
That needs to happen for Si-on to go
tumbling head over heels in misery.

483
00:28:57,153 --> 00:29:00,072
At this rate,
he won't even manage a single roly-poly.

484
00:29:00,156 --> 00:29:01,907
But, more than that,

485
00:29:03,159 --> 00:29:04,285
aren't I the lead character?

486
00:29:04,910 --> 00:29:07,371
Right now, Si-on is coming across
as the obsessive top.

487
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:12,751
Not at all.

488
00:29:12,835 --> 00:29:15,838
No way. Of course not.

489
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:20,342
It's just, as I was writing it,

490
00:29:20,426 --> 00:29:23,804
I felt like I should change
the flow of the narrative.

491
00:29:24,305 --> 00:29:26,307
In that way, how can I put it…

492
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,976
The characters will go through
a wider range of emotions,

493
00:29:29,059 --> 00:29:31,187
and the story itself will be more diverse.

494
00:29:32,229 --> 00:29:33,230
But the thing is…

495
00:29:34,231 --> 00:29:35,232
Just a moment.

496
00:29:41,947 --> 00:29:44,783
Do I really have to change this
for you to feel validated?

497
00:29:55,419 --> 00:29:56,462
Fine.

498
00:29:57,379 --> 00:29:59,423
You're doing great.

499
00:29:59,507 --> 00:30:01,050
Fine, now if everybody

500
00:30:01,133 --> 00:30:03,177
can just hang in there!

501
00:30:04,178 --> 00:30:05,679
-Let's get back to it.
-Okay.

502
00:30:05,763 --> 00:30:07,640
-Let's do this.
-From the top.

503
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:09,558
I'm fine with that.

504
00:30:10,726 --> 00:30:12,811
-We're doing this again?
-From now on,

505
00:30:13,771 --> 00:30:15,814
I'm going to be your personal bitch.

506
00:30:23,030 --> 00:30:24,198
Is this right?

507
00:30:24,281 --> 00:30:27,910
What the heck? I can't even write
my own novel how I want.

508
00:30:31,372 --> 00:30:32,498
Hang on.

509
00:30:33,499 --> 00:30:35,751
He's only checking the original file.

510
00:30:39,129 --> 00:30:40,589
That's much better.

511
00:30:40,673 --> 00:30:42,132
Really?

512
00:30:42,216 --> 00:30:43,050
Upload it.

513
00:30:55,354 --> 00:30:57,940
WE WERE FRIENDS
EPISODE 4 REAL

514
00:31:00,442 --> 00:31:01,277
EPISODE 4 REAL

515
00:31:01,944 --> 00:31:02,820
WE WERE FRIENDS

516
00:31:07,616 --> 00:31:08,576
SUBMIT A NEW PROJECT

517
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:13,372
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 4

518
00:31:30,014 --> 00:31:33,434
There's no way he'll check online.

519
00:31:33,517 --> 00:31:35,060
Like he'd ever look up We Were Friends.

520
00:31:35,644 --> 00:31:36,770
-Not him.
-You little…

521
00:31:36,854 --> 00:31:38,063
Today's the day.

522
00:31:38,147 --> 00:31:39,315
Check your students' uniforms

523
00:31:39,398 --> 00:31:40,858
and make sure
they're on their best behavior.

524
00:31:40,941 --> 00:31:43,235
Let's make sure this is a success.

525
00:31:43,319 --> 00:31:45,112
-What's going on?
-Film him on the sly?

526
00:31:45,195 --> 00:31:46,905
I'll keep it a secret.

527
00:31:46,989 --> 00:31:48,073
I know everything.

528
00:31:48,157 --> 00:31:51,160
If you're not going to cooperate,
you leave me no choice.

529
00:31:51,243 --> 00:31:53,454
Why are you going this far?
You're going to regret this.

530
00:31:53,537 --> 00:31:55,205
Are you going to betray my trust?

531
00:31:55,289 --> 00:31:56,540
-I'll figure it out by myself.
-Try that, then.

532
00:31:56,624 --> 00:31:59,752
What am I going to do now, Mr. Ga?

533
00:31:59,835 --> 00:32:01,837
Shall I just transfer?

534
00:32:57,976 --> 00:32:59,978
Subtitle: Paul Carver

